==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Farrier
<hw>Far"ri*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>farrour</ets>, <ets>ferrer</ets>, OF. <ets>ferreor</ets>,
<ets>ferrier</ets>, LL. <ets>Ferrator</ets>, <ets>ferrarius
equorum</ets>, from <ets>ferrare</ets> to shoe a horse,
<ets>ferrum</ets> a horseshoe, fr. L. <ets>ferrum</ets> iron. Cf.
<er>Ferreous</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A shoer of horses; a
veterinary surgeon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Farrier</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Farrier
<hw>Far"ri*er</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To practice as a farrier; to
carry on the trade of a farrier.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Mortimer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Farriery</ent>⟦br⟧
